727014f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 126th and 127th Streets, showing the Armbruster farmhouse, now gone, known as the Peter Opper Roadhouse in 1891. See view west from 130th Street for more
data.
About 1900
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

725841f-a.text:
126th Street, east side, between Jamaica Ave. (left) and Eighty-ninth Ave. (right), showing partially in the background the James H. Elmor house from 1870 to 1891. This information is verified by T.F. Archer. However the Queens Atlas of 1891 shows this property as that of James Elmilie.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727013f-b.text:
(1)
Jamaica Ave. (right foreground not shown), at the N.E. corner of 126th Street, showing the former home of Capt. W.A. Lighthall. This place was operated as a hotel by P. Opper in 1891. In 1922 it was known the Jamaica Saewgerbund Hotel operated by Mrs. Kaesebart.
It was demolished in March 1926.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, another angle.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same snowing another view of the same house.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
